// Semantic direction:
// navigasjonskart is a graph of walkable nodes used by pathfinding algorithms.
// nk_fra_kart builds a navigation graph from a tilemap, marking passable tiles as nodes.
// astar implements A* pathfinding; the heuristic guides search toward the goal.
// manhattan_avstand is efficient for grid maps; euklidsk_avstand is better for free movement.
// astar_sti is the sequence of nodes from start to goal; astar_kostnad is the total path cost.
// navmesh is a polygon mesh describing walkable surfaces in 3D; nm_recast builds it from geometry.
// nm_detour is the runtime pathfinding library on a navmesh.
// nm_glatt_sti applies string pulling to remove unnecessary waypoints from a path.
// sti_følging steers an agent along a path; sf_dreieradius prevents sharp turns.
// sf_oppdater_sf advances the agent toward sf_steg and updates sf_fremgang.
// crowds uses Reciprocal Velocity Obstacles (RVO2) for local collision avoidance between many agents.
// ca_unngå_kollisjoner steers each crowd agent to avoid others without global coordination.
// atferd_tre is a hierarchical behavior tree; bt_sekvens runs children until one fails.
// bt_velger runs children until one succeeds (fallback / priority selector).
// bt_parallel_bt runs all children simultaneously; completion depends on policy.
// bt_betingelse checks a predicate; bt_handling executes a leaf behavior.
// tilstandsmaskin_ai is a simpler alternative to behavior trees for basic AI.
// syn_sensor checks line-of-sight and angle; hørsel_sensor checks proximity to sound sources.
// minneoppføring records the last known position of a detected entity.

// Primitive flow:
// pathfinding: astar_finn(start, mål, nk) → sti (list of posisjoner)
//   sti_følging: every frame: sf_oppdater → steer toward next waypoint
//   sm_glatt_sti: remove collinear waypoints using visibility tests
// behavior tree: bt_kjør(rot) → DFS:
//   bt_sekvens: run child1 → success → run child2 → failure → return failure
//   bt_betingelse("kan_se(fiende)") → true → bt_handling("chase") → bt_suksess

// This defines navigation graphs, A* pathfinding, navmesh pathfinding with string
// pulling, crowd simulation with RVO2, behavior trees, and sensor-based AI.
